section.section:
The value of net capital for each year for purposes of subsection (1) of this section shall be determined by:
Adding together the book value of:
Capital stock paid in;
Surplus;
Undivided profits and capital reserves;
Net unrealized holding gains or losses on available for sale securities; and
Cumulative foreign currency translation adjustments; and
Deducting from the total determined under subparagraph 1. of this subsection an amount equal to the same percentage of the total as the book value of United States obligations and Kentucky obligations bears to the book value of the total assets of the financial institution.
